      <h3>How to play Goalmine</h3>

      <h4>A quick tour</h4>
      <p>Goalmine is built around match weeks. The week starts on a Saturday and ends on a Friday. 12 matches will be chosen for each week, one of which will be the <acronym title="Game of the Week">GotW</acronym>. The matches chosen will nearly always take place Saturday to Wednesday. The main list of weeks is found on the <a href="/weeks">fixtures</a> menu. From here you can see the standings and predictions for that week.</p>
      <p>The 'this week' menu icon will always take you to the predictions for the current week. This is either the calendar week you're in, or the following week if the last match for this week has already been played.</p>
      <p>The standings page shows the players' positions for that week. The predictions page shows a grid of all players' predictions for each match, along with the total predicted goals.</p>
      <p>The options screen allows you to update your details/change your password, invite a friend to take part, see your balance or logout. There are additional options available if you are an administrator.</p>
      <p>Many elements in the various screens are clickable for more information. You can click on:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Teams (e.g. <a href="/teams/19">West Ham</a>)</li>
        <li>Matches (e.g. <a href="/matches/97">Manchester City v Arsenal</a> 23<sup>rd</sup> Sep)</li>
        <li>Leagues (e.g. <a href="/leagues/11">La Liga</a>)</li>
        <li>Users (e.g. <a href="/users/1">Me</a>)</li>
      </ul>
       <p>to see more information about that item. For instance, clicking on <a href="/teams/19">West Ham</a> will show you a list of Goalmine matches involving West Ham, and the results.</p>

      <h4>Making predictions</h3>
      <p>To edit your predictions, click on the link at the bottom of the predictions screen.</p>
      <p>From the edit screen, you can make predictions for each match. Scores should be entered separated by a dash (-). You must choose one match to be your Joker (double points).</p>
      <p>You can only make or edit predictions up to midday of each Saturday. You can also move your Joker as many times as you wish, but once your chosen joker match has played, you can no longer move it.</p>

      <h4>What's the score?</h4>
      <p>You can find out scores in a number of ways. Clicking on any player will show their weekly score in a graph, along with the number of wins they have. Clicking a bar in the graph will take you to that week. From the fixtures page you can see the standings for any particular week, showing all players' scores. Once the league has started you will be able to click on the menu icon to see the overall league table.</p>

      <h4>Balances</h4>
      <p>You can see your current balance at any time from the options screen. From that screen you can also see a list of all transactions, including all weekly entries and any winnings and deposits.</p>
  
